cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the use of deep neural networks for image processing, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of generators to incorporate top-down information into the network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores the use of zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of generators to improve classification performance also falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses data augmentation, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL), but can also be applied to image processing.
